cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes an extension to a popular deep learning optimization routine, Adam, and investigates its performance from a statistical moments perspective. It also conducts experiments to compare the proposed method with the vanilla Adam algorithm. 

It could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with optimization methods for deep learning, which is a common application of neural networks. 

The paper also mentions experiments on image classification tasks, which suggests it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

As the paper proposes an optimization method for deep learning, it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Finally, the paper involves statistical analysis and experiments, which could also make it relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
